// Issue #2651 accept side: a legal callee-frame bare alias reaching the unique
// registered-owner scan. `framealias.make()` returns its result spelled bare
// (`Widget`) in the callee's own frame; the local `read` parameter is typed
// with the module-qualified `framealias.Widget`. Both name the SAME definition.
//
// Because this is a plain import (no `::{ Widget }` opt-in), the bare `Widget`
// is not a published bare binding, so the owner-identity gate qualifies it
// through the UNIQUE registered-owner scan (`type_defs`/`known_types` →
// `framealias.Widget`) rather than the published-bare path. The gate must
// ACCEPT the resulting owner-identical pairing — a false reject here would
// break every legitimate callee-frame / prelude bare alias.
//
// Harness verb: hew run
// Expected: 11 — the callee-frame `Widget` flows through the qualified-typed
// parameter unchanged.
import hew::framealias;

fn read(w: framealias.Widget) -> i64 {
    w.tag
}

fn main() {
    println(f"{read(framealias.make())}");
}
